title <size:18>UNIX File Search API (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: find /home -name "*.java" -size +1M -type f -modified 7 | sort -by size | limit 20</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class FileSearchService <<Facade>> {
    - fileSystem : FileSystem
    - traversalStrategy : TraversalStrategy
    --
    + search(params) : SearchResult
    + search(rootDir, filter) : SearchResult
    + search(rootDir, filter, sort, limit) : SearchResult
    + count(rootDir, filter) : long
    + exists(rootDir, filter) : boolean
    + findFirst(rootDir, filter) : File
}

note top of FileSearchService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Think of the UNIX find command.
    Client calls search(rootDir, filter).
    **Facade** hides file system traversal,
    filter application, sorting, and
    result collection behind one API."

    "find /home -name '*.java' -size +1M
    becomes: search('/home',
      And(NameFilter, SizeFilter))"
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: FILE SYSTEM MODEL — Composite Pattern
' ====================================================================
abstract class FileSystemEntry {
    - name : String
    - path : String
    - size : long
    - createdAt : LocalDateTime
    - modifiedAt : LocalDateTime
    - permissions : Set<Permission>
    - owner : String
    - group : String
    --
    + getName() : String
    + getPath() : String
    + getSize() : long
    + getModifiedAt() : LocalDateTime
    + getPermissions() : Set<Permission>
    + getOwner() : String
    + isHidden() : boolean
    + {abstract} isDirectory() : boolean
    + {abstract} getType() : FileType
}

class File {
    - extension : String
    - mimeType : String
    - content : byte[]
    --
    + isDirectory() : boolean
    + getType() : FileType
    + getExtension() : String
    + getMimeType() : String
}

class Directory {
    - children : List<FileSystemEntry>
    --
    + isDirectory() : boolean
    + getType() : FileType
    + getChildren() : List<FileSystemEntry>
    + addChild(entry) : void
    + removeChild(name) : void
    + getChildCount() : int
}

class SymLink {
    - target : FileSystemEntry
    --
    + isDirectory() : boolean
    + getType() : FileType
    + getTarget() : FileSystemEntry
    + resolveTarget() : FileSystemEntry
}

enum FileType {
    REGULAR_FILE
    DIRECTORY
    SYMLINK
    PIPE
    SOCKET
    BLOCK_DEVICE
}

enum Permission {
    OWNER_READ
    OWNER_WRITE
    OWNER_EXECUTE
    GROUP_READ
    GROUP_WRITE
    GROUP_EXECUTE
    OTHER_READ
    OTHER_WRITE
    OTHER_EXECUTE
}

note top of FileSystemEntry #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - File system is a tree.**
    "**Composite Pattern**: File and Directory
    share the same base class FileSystemEntry.
    Directory contains a list of children
    (Files or other Directories).
    SymLink points to another entry."

    "This mirrors real UNIX: everything is
    an inode. Directory is just a special file
    that contains other entries. Traversal
    treats files and directories uniformly."
    **Pattern: Composite | LSP**
end note

FileSystemEntry <|-- File
FileSystemEntry <|-- Directory
FileSystemEntry <|-- SymLink
Directory o--> FileSystemEntry : children >
SymLink --> FileSystemEntry : target >
FileSystemEntry --> FileType
FileSystemEntry --> Permission : has >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: FILE SYSTEM ABSTRACTION
' ====================================================================
interface FileSystem <<Strategy>> {
    + getRoot() : Directory
    + getEntry(path) : FileSystemEntry
    + exists(path) : boolean
    + listDirectory(path) : List<FileSystemEntry>
}

class LocalFileSystem {
    - rootPath : String
    --
    + getRoot() : Directory
    + getEntry(path) : FileSystemEntry
    + listDirectory(path) : List<FileSystemEntry>
}

class InMemoryFileSystem {
    - root : Directory
    --
    + getRoot() : Directory
    + getEntry(path) : FileSystemEntry
    + addFile(path, file) : void
    + listDirectory(path) : List<FileSystemEntry>
}

class RemoteFileSystem {
    - host : String
    - connection : Connection
    --
    + getRoot() : Directory
    + getEntry(path) : FileSystemEntry
    + listDirectory(path) : List<FileSystemEntry>
}

note bottom of FileSystem #C8E6C9
    **STEP 3 - Where are the files?**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — file system source
    is pluggable. LocalFileSystem reads from
    actual disk. InMemoryFileSystem for tests.
    RemoteFileSystem for networked (NFS/SSH)."
    **Pattern: Strategy | DIP, OCP**
end note

FileSystem <|.. LocalFileSystem
FileSystem <|.. InMemoryFileSystem
FileSystem <|.. RemoteFileSystem
FileSearchService --> FileSystem : reads from >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: FILTER INTERFACE — Core Abstraction (Strategy)
' ====================================================================
interface Filter <<Strategy>> {
    + apply(entry : FileSystemEntry) : boolean
}

note top of Filter #FFE0B2
    **STEP 4 - The core abstraction. (KEY)**
    "One interface, one method:
    apply(entry) -> boolean.
    Returns true if entry matches.
    Every filter — simple or complex —
    implements this. The entire system
    is built around this single interface."
    **Pattern: Strategy | ISP, OCP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: CONCRETE FILTERS — Leaf Strategies
' ====================================================================
class NameFilter {
    - pattern : String
    - caseSensitive : boolean
    - regex : boolean
    --
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

class ExtensionFilter {
    - extensions : Set<String>
    --
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

class SizeFilter {
    - minBytes : long
    - maxBytes : long
    - operator : ComparisonOp
    --
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

class TypeFilter {
    - type : FileType
    --
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

class ModifiedDateFilter {
    - after : LocalDateTime
    - before : LocalDateTime
    - withinDays : int
    --
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

class PermissionFilter {
    - requiredPermissions : Set<Permission>
    --
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

class OwnerFilter {
    - ownerName : String
    --
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

class DepthFilter {
    - maxDepth : int
    - currentDepth : int
    --
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

class HiddenFileFilter {
    - includeHidden : boolean
    --
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

class ContentFilter {
    - searchText : String
    - regex : boolean
    --
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

enum ComparisonOp {
    GREATER_THAN
    LESS_THAN
    EQUAL_TO
    BETWEEN
}

note bottom of NameFilter #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - One filter per criterion.**
    "Maps to UNIX find flags:
    **-name** -> NameFilter (glob/regex)
    **-extension** -> ExtensionFilter (.java, .py)
    **-size** -> SizeFilter (+1M, -100K)
    **-type f/d** -> TypeFilter (FILE/DIR)
    **-mtime** -> ModifiedDateFilter (-7 days)
    **-perm** -> PermissionFilter (755)
    **-user** -> OwnerFilter
    **-maxdepth** -> DepthFilter
    **-content** -> ContentFilter (like grep)"

    "Each is independent, testable, single
    responsibility. Add InodeFilter? One class."
    **Pattern: Strategy | SRP, OCP**
end note

Filter <|.. NameFilter
Filter <|.. ExtensionFilter
Filter <|.. SizeFilter
Filter <|.. TypeFilter
Filter <|.. ModifiedDateFilter
Filter <|.. PermissionFilter
Filter <|.. OwnerFilter
Filter <|.. DepthFilter
Filter <|.. HiddenFileFilter
Filter <|.. ContentFilter
SizeFilter --> ComparisonOp


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: COMPOSITE FILTERS — AND / OR / NOT
' ====================================================================
class AndFilter {
    - filters : List<Filter>
    --
    + AndFilter(filters)
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

class OrFilter {
    - filters : List<Filter>
    --
    + OrFilter(filters)
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

class NotFilter {
    - filter : Filter
    --
    + NotFilter(filter)
    + apply(entry) : boolean
}

note top of AndFilter #FFCDD2
    **STEP 6 - Combine filters. (KEY STEP)**
    "**Composite Pattern** — And, Or, Not are
    themselves Filters. Same interface."

    "UNIX: find -name '*.java' -size +1M
    = And(NameFilter('*.java'), SizeFilter(>1M))"

    "UNIX: find -name '*.java' -o -name '*.kt'
    = Or(NameFilter('*.java'), NameFilter('*.kt'))"

    "UNIX: find ! -name '*.class'
    = Not(NameFilter('*.class'))"

    "Nest arbitrarily:
    And(SizeFilter, Or(ExtFilter, NameFilter))
    Infinite composability, zero new code."
    **Pattern: Composite | OCP, LSP**
end note

Filter <|.. AndFilter
Filter <|.. OrFilter
Filter <|.. NotFilter
AndFilter o--> Filter : children >
OrFilter o--> Filter : children >
NotFilter o--> Filter : wraps >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: TRAVERSAL — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface TraversalStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + traverse(root, filter, visitor) : void
}

class BFSTraversal {
    --
    + traverse(root, filter, visitor) : void
}

class DFSTraversal {
    --
    + traverse(root, filter, visitor) : void
}

class ParallelTraversal {
    - threadCount : int
    --
    + traverse(root, filter, visitor) : void
}

class MaxDepthTraversal {
    - maxDepth : int
    --
    + traverse(root, filter, visitor) : void
}

interface FileVisitor <<Visitor>> {
    + visit(entry) : void
}

class CollectingVisitor {
    - results : List<FileSystemEntry>
    --
    + visit(entry) : void
    + getResults() : List<FileSystemEntry>
}

class CountingVisitor {
    - count : long
    --
    + visit(entry) : void
    + getCount() : long
}

class FirstMatchVisitor {
    - found : FileSystemEntry
    --
    + visit(entry) : void
    + getResult() : FileSystemEntry
    + isFound() : boolean
}

note bottom of TraversalStrategy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 7 - How to walk the tree?**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — traversal is pluggable.
    **DFS**: depth-first (default, like real find).
    **BFS**: breadth-first (find closest matches).
    **Parallel**: multi-threaded for huge trees.
    **MaxDepth**: stop at N levels."

    "**Visitor Pattern** — what to do with matches.
    **CollectingVisitor**: gather all results.
    **CountingVisitor**: just count (like find | wc -l).
    **FirstMatchVisitor**: stop at first hit."
    **Patterns: Strategy + Visitor | OCP, SRP**
end note

TraversalStrategy <|.. BFSTraversal
TraversalStrategy <|.. DFSTraversal
TraversalStrategy <|.. ParallelTraversal
TraversalStrategy <|.. MaxDepthTraversal
TraversalStrategy --> FileVisitor : uses >
FileVisitor <|.. CollectingVisitor
FileVisitor <|.. CountingVisitor
FileVisitor <|.. FirstMatchVisitor
FileSearchService --> TraversalStrategy : delegates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: SEARCH PARAMS + BUILDER — Fluent API
' ====================================================================
class SearchParams {
    - rootDirectory : String
    - filter : Filter
    - sortStrategy : SortStrategy
    - maxResults : int
    - traversal : TraversalStrategy
    - followSymlinks : boolean
    --
    + getRootDirectory() : String
    + getFilter() : Filter
}

class SearchParamsBuilder <<Builder>> {
    - rootDir : String
    - filters : List<Filter>
    - sortStrategy : SortStrategy
    - maxResults : int
    - traversal : TraversalStrategy
    - followSymlinks : boolean
    --
    + root(path) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + name(pattern) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + extension(exts) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + minSize(bytes) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + maxSize(bytes) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + type(fileType) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + modifiedWithinDays(days) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + owner(name) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + maxDepth(depth) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + excludeHidden() : SearchParamsBuilder
    + containsText(text) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + or(filter) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + not(filter) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + sortBy(strategy) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + limit(max) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + parallel(threads) : SearchParamsBuilder
    + followSymlinks() : SearchParamsBuilder
    + build() : SearchParams
}

note bottom of SearchParamsBuilder #D1C4E9
    **STEP 8 - Fluent API for humans.**
    "Constructing And(Name, Size, Type) by
    hand is verbose. **Builder Pattern**:"

    "new SearchParamsBuilder()
      .root('/home')
      .extension('java', 'kt')
      .minSize(1_000_000)
      .modifiedWithinDays(7)
      .type(REGULAR_FILE)
      .excludeHidden()
      .sortBy(new SortBySize())
      .limit(20)
      .build()"

    "Maps to UNIX:
    find /home -name '*.java' -o -name '*.kt'
      -size +1M -mtime -7 -type f
      | sort -by-size | head -20"
    **Pattern: Builder | SRP**
end note

SearchParamsBuilder --> SearchParams : builds >
SearchParams --> Filter : contains >
SearchParams --> TraversalStrategy


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 9: SORT + RESULT
' ====================================================================
interface SortStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + sort(entries) : List<FileSystemEntry>
}

class SortByName {
    - ascending : boolean
    --
    + sort(entries) : List<FileSystemEntry>
}

class SortBySize {
    - ascending : boolean
    --
    + sort(entries) : List<FileSystemEntry>
}

class SortByModifiedDate {
    - ascending : boolean
    --
    + sort(entries) : List<FileSystemEntry>
}

class SortByPath {
    --
    + sort(entries) : List<FileSystemEntry>
}

class SearchResult {
    - matches : List<FileSystemEntry>
    - totalScanned : long
    - matchCount : long
    - searchTimeMs : long
    - truncated : boolean
    --
    + getMatches() : List<FileSystemEntry>
    + getMatchCount() : long
    + getSearchTimeMs() : long
    + isTruncated() : boolean
}

note bottom of SortStrategy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 9 - Sort + result.**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — sorting is pluggable.
    By name, size, date, path. Like ls -lS."

    "**SearchResult** includes metadata:
    totalScanned, matchCount, searchTimeMs,
    truncated (if limit was hit). Transparent."
end note

SortStrategy <|.. SortByName
SortStrategy <|.. SortBySize
SortStrategy <|.. SortByModifiedDate
SortStrategy <|.. SortByPath
FileSearchService --> SortStrategy : sorts with >
FileSearchService --> SearchResult : returns >
SearchResult o--> FileSystemEntry : matches >
SearchParams --> SortStrategy


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "UNIX file system is a tree (**Composite**: File + Directory
    share one base). Filters are the core: one interface apply(entry) -> bool.
    Leaf filters (name, size, type, date, owner) are **Strategies**. AndFilter,
    OrFilter, NotFilter compose them (**Composite** — same interface). Tree
    traversal is pluggable: DFS/BFS/Parallel (**Strategy**). Visitor decides
    what to do with matches. Builder gives fluent API.
    6 patterns: **Composite** (x2: FS tree + filter tree), **Strategy** (x4),
    **Visitor**, **Builder**, **Facade**."
end note


